        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>Helps user understand their billing and payment details. This topic is triggered when the user asks for the payment plan for any invoice, details about an invoice in context, the next payment for an account, or information in an account’s billing context. It also handles requests to retrieve the latest invoice, download the invoice document or PDF, or check the current account balance. The topic intelligently identifies the correct billing flow or action to execute — such as fetching payment schedules, generating invoice documents, or retrieving account balances — ensuring users receive accurate, contextual, and actionable responses about their billing information.</description>
        <developerName>BillingInquiries_16jak000001aGld</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>To retrieve and summarize the net account balance by aggregating posted invoices, credit memos, debit memos, payments, and refunds call action GetAccountBalance.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>To identify and summarize the next payment due date and amount by referencing outstanding invoices and payment schedules for an account call action GetNextDuePayment.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction2</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 2</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>To display the  payment plans for a specified invoice call action GetPaymentPlanDetails.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction3</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 3</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>To fetch and provide the most recent posted invoice along with its associated document for the provided account call action InvoiceDocumentPDF.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction4</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 4</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Use Markdown formatting for responses. If an output variable or field value begins with /sfc/servlet.shepherd/document/download/, treat it as a downloadable file link. Automatically prepend the current Salesforce org domain (for example, https://mydomain.my.salesforce.com) to create the full download URL.Display the link in a user-friendly format such as: You can download the PDF here: [Download Invoice PDF](https://mydomain.my.salesforce.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/069Wt000001qSu5IAE) Do not display the raw URL or ID; always format it as a clickable Markdown hyperlink.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction5</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 5</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Pick up this topic if user asks for the payment plan for any invoice or invoice&apos;s context or next payment for an account or in an account&apos;s context or asks to get Latest Invoice and/or Document/PDF/ downloadable PDF, account balance for an account or in account&apos;s context.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction6</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 6</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>5</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Check if the user has provided a account name. If so, use it as the accountName for the GetAccountBalance and GetNextDuePayment action and as varAccountName for InvoiceDocumentPDF action. If the user is on the record or Lightning page of the Account object, use the currentRecordId as the varAccountId for the InvoiceDocumentPDF, GetAccountBalance and GetNextDuePayment actions. If the accountName/varAccountName or varAccountId can’t be located, prompt the user to provide it</description>
            <developerName>Instruction7</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 7</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>6</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Check if the user has provided a invoice document number. If so, use it as the varInvoiceDocNumber for the GetPaymentPlanDetails action. If the user is on the record or Lightning page of the Invoice object, use the currentRecordId as the varInvoiceId for the GetPaymentPlanDetails actions. If the varInvoiceDocNumber or varInvoiceId can’t be located, prompt the user to provide it</description>
            <developerName>Instruction8</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 8</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>7</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Never display internal Salesforce record IDs to the end user. When referencing Salesforce records in responses: Always present human-readable fields (such as Name, Number, or Label) instead of IDs. If a record is linkable, render it as a clickable link using the record’s display name, not its ID. Invoices must always be referenced by their Document Number, and the Document Number should be the clickable text. Do not expose IDs in plain text, hyperlinks, error messages, logs, or explanations under any circumstance.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction9</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 9</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>8</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
